[00:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Welcome back. I have been searching the&nbsp; internet on how to do FPV videos for a&nbsp;&nbsp; long time. Until yesterday, luckily I found&nbsp; this LoRA which has been added very recently,&nbsp;&nbsp; which, according to the upload comment,&nbsp; has been modified to run in ComfyUI. So,&nbsp;&nbsp; I figured why not test it and share my findings?&nbsp; The repo itself does not have any details, except&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for "A smoother FPV lens for low-speed flight".&nbsp; But my findings were a bit surprising, as it\'s&nbsp;&nbsp; not necessarily always at low speed. In fact, the&nbsp; FPV itself were shot at lower angles most of the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'time. So, let\'s get to a quick walkthrough of my&nbsp; workflow. The workflow is a 2-pass or -stage one,&nbsp;&nbsp; where we use the latent upscale model to increase&nbsp; the resolution. This way, we might get a bit of a&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lesser quality output, compared to a 1-pass&nbsp; where we generate a high resolution at once,&nbsp;&nbsp; but at a much faster speed, even with high&nbsp; resolutions as 1920 by 1080. Here are the&nbsp;&nbsp; links to all required models. Pick the size of&nbsp; LTX model that fits your VRAM. You can just pick&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one for all models with options. Place them inside&nbsp; the subfolders listed at the end of each category,&nbsp;&nbsp; and map the folders to this chart. Here are&nbsp; the split files loaders. Select either the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'safetensors loader or the GGUF loaders. I&nbsp; have not included safetensors clip loaders,&nbsp;&nbsp; as I think the encoder files are much smaller&nbsp; for the GGUF variants. And as for the force or&nbsp;&nbsp; set clip device, you may want to bypass or delete&nbsp; it if you don\'t do offloading to a second GPU. &nbsp;'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Load your LoRA\'s here. Bypass the first loader&nbsp; to use the distilled acceleration LoRA if you&nbsp;&nbsp; use the dev model. And bypass the third loader&nbsp; to stack an additional LoRA you might want to&nbsp;&nbsp; test. Here we load our images. Also, we set our&nbsp; video output resolution here. According to my&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'previous LTX tests, I needed to load a blank or&nbsp; black image for text to video generations even I&nbsp;&nbsp; have toggled the bypass image condition switch.&nbsp; It occasionally uses the reference image that is&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pre-loaded as it\'s first frame for generation, and&nbsp; suddenly switches to a totally different scene for&nbsp;&nbsp; the rest of the video. Don\'t know why, so I just&nbsp; load a black image so the video starts out with&nbsp;&nbsp; a black scene and fades into the actual video.&nbsp; Then we resize the image to half it\'s resolution,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which will be upscaled later in the 2nd stage.&nbsp; And here are the main settings for FPS, length&nbsp;&nbsp; and the text to video or image to video switch.&nbsp; We enter our prompt here. I have tested with&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'many keywords but this phrase seems to work almost&nbsp; 100%. Just copy and paste it here. Then, below we&nbsp;&nbsp; set whether to use the free API online or offline&nbsp; encoding. You can bypass the whole group if not&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'needed, or leave them without any errors. Reconnect the wires for both positive and negative&nbsp;&nbsp; prompts like this for local clip text encoding, or&nbsp; like so for online API. Do not forget to enter the&nbsp;&nbsp; API key here. Use the link provided here to apply&nbsp; for the free API key with a google account. Also,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'do not forget to select the text projection file&nbsp; here. And here are the groups for preprocessing,&nbsp;&nbsp; first and second sampling stages. Here, at the&nbsp; decoding stage you may want to switch from regular&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'full VAE decoding to tiled decoding by doing&nbsp; so. Hold shift and click to drag the output&nbsp;&nbsp; connections to reroute them like this. And just&nbsp; drag these to their respective input sockets.&nbsp;&nbsp; After decoding, down here I have included VFI&nbsp; and RTX upscaling for testing. To interpolate 2x,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'enter 2 here. And to upscale further, enter a&nbsp; multiplier here. Both groups, consisting of 5&nbsp;&nbsp; nodes, can be bypassed without error. I have&nbsp; tested and so far, results are good and very&nbsp;&nbsp; fast. Here are the 6 VFI models you can choose&nbsp; from. I have added a note down here for a bit of&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'details on the models. And here are your upscaling&nbsp; options. I do not prefer ultimate as it produces&nbsp;&nbsp; too much sharpness, which I do not like. Let\'s do a quick test run to see if the workflow&nbsp;&nbsp; actually works. More samples are coming up.&nbsp; And in my opinion, I really like this LoRA.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I have been searching for this motion LoRA&nbsp; for quite some time. I really hope you liked&nbsp;&nbsp; this video and the LoRA. Please like and&nbsp; subscribe, and also share this if you find&nbsp;&nbsp; it helpful in any way. It will help me a lot.&nbsp; Thanks again for watching, and see you soon.'
